    "Venous blood samples of approximately 3 ml were obtained from all participants and subsequently centrifuged at 3000 rpm for 10 minutes to isolate serum. The serum samples from 100 individuals with nasopharyngeal carcinoma and 100 healthy individuals were analyzed for BNLF2b antibodies using a fully automated chemiluminescent immunoassay analyzer (Wan200+ model) manufactured by Xiamen Youmaike Medical Instrument Co., Ltd. The EB virus BNLF2b antibody assay kit was utilized as the reagent. VCA-IgA, Rta-IgG, and Zta-IgA antibody levels in the serum were quantified through the ELISA technique. All experimental steps strictly adhered to the manufacturer&#39;s guidelines.",
    "Statistical analyses were conducted utilizing SPSS software version 16.0. Graphs were generated with SPSS 16.0 and GraphPad Prism 9.5. Measurement data, determined to be non-normally distributed, were presented as medians and analyzed using the rank-sum test. Count data were represented as rates and analyzed through the chi-square test, with a significance threshold of P &lt; 0.05. Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC) curves were constructed to establish the optimal cutoff value based on the maximum Youden index. Additionally, the ROC curve was utilized to calculate the area under the curve (AUC), confidence intervals (CI), sensitivity, and specificity of the diagnostic techniques."
